Package com.precog.client

Contains PrecogClient, simple Java client for working with Precog.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Format
    Used to specify the format of some data to be inserted into Precog.
    FormatVisitor<A>
    This defines a type-safe way to work with the valid Precog formats.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AccountInfo
    User account details (email, account ID, API key, root path, etc.).
    AccountPlan
    User account plan.
    AppendResult
    The result of appending data to Precog (success status, errors, etc.).
    DelimitedFormat
    A CSV format represents CSV files as values separated by a delimiter, a quotation character used to quote values, and a character to escape quotes within a quoted value.
    Formats  
    PrecogClient
    A simple REST client for storing data in Precog and querying it with Quirrel.
    Query
    A representation of a running, asynchronous query.
    QueryResult
    Result of the execution of a query (result set, errors, warnings, etc).
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    JsonFormat
    This class represents JSON formatted data.
